==English==
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Lazarus'''
#(''New Testament'') A man brought back to life by [[Jesus]] after being in the [[tomb]] for four days
# In the [[New Testament]], the brother of [[Mary]] and [[Martha]].

===Verb===
'''Lazarus'''
# To rescue a dying person.
# To raise from the dead.
Usage note: The verb ''Lazarus'' is written with capital letters. It is also considered AAVE.
